{"id":14881829,"mediaExerciseId":"7010948c-559e-45ba-96d8-ad87f4abfd5e","exerciseName":"13","chapterName":"23","chapterTitle":"Enterprise Risk Management","groupId":612487,"groupTitle":"Critical Thinking Questions","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":787,"solutions":[{"id":6008997,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this problem, we will be presented with different scenarios and we need to come up with the best hedging strategy for each scenario.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"A futures contract is a type of agreement/contract between two parties wherein they put in a standardized legal agreement to buy/sell a certain product for a certain price in the future. This is done as a way to crosshedge or to leverage possible risks in the future where the price for a product or commodity may not be ideal. ","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"**a.** To offset possible losses, the company needs to buy futures of the components that they are using, particularly, the component that is the most costly. ","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":105,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/12/5523d96a696568862503b777375e6c65/9edb1eaa86cee82fe1bedcfbbab1db57/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":53,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/12/5523d96a696568862503b777375e6c65/9edb1eaa86cee82fe1bedcfbbab1db57/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3},{"columns":[{"text":"**b.** To offset possible losses, the company needs to buy futures of the components that they are using. In this case, they need to buy futures contracts of sugar. ","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":105,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/12/5523d96a696568862503b777375e6c65/d9699e91246b7e3bd68a124637d3a987/lateximg_large.png","width":996},"regular":{"height":53,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/12/5523d96a696568862503b777375e6c65/d9699e91246b7e3bd68a124637d3a987/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":4},{"columns":[{"text":"**c.** Since the farmer is anticipating a high number of yield, this means that the prices will go down. In order to offset this, they need to sell futures contract of the corn. ","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":100,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/12/5523d96a696568862503b777375e6c65/476eb842fb4a3290b0c742b944a0efee/lateximg_large.png","width":996},"regular":{"height":51,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/12/5523d96a696568862503b777375e6c65/476eb842fb4a3290b0c742b944a0efee/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":5},{"columns":[{"text":"**d.** To offset possible losses, the company needs to buy futures of the components that they are using, particularly, the component that is the most costly. ","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":105,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/12/5523d96a696568862503b777375e6c65/837d3cef484ea867f16f0f6193fb2651/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":53,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/12/5523d96a696568862503b777375e6c65/837d3cef484ea867f16f0f6193fb2651/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":6},{"columns":[{"text":"**e.** Since they are anticipating an excess supply, this means that the prices will go down. In order to offset this, they need to sell futures contract of the natural gas. ","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":105,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/12/5523d96a696568862503b777375e6c65/0b3823444b977639bef162b8d4898a1e/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":53,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/12/5523d96a696568862503b777375e6c65/0b3823444b977639bef162b8d4898a1e/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":7},{"columns":[{"text":"**f.** Since they get their profit from fixed-rate interests, they should buy futures contracts of bonds. This will protect them if ever the interest rates go down since bonds and interest moves in the opposite direction. ","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":105,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/12/5523d96a696568862503b777375e6c65/d2ac695fb0df83d13c63bfba0a95c151/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":53,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/12/5523d96a696568862503b777375e6c65/d2ac695fb0df83d13c63bfba0a95c151/lateximg.png","width":499}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":8},{"columns":[{"text":"**g.** In order to hedge against the decline of the price of their stocks in the market, they need to sell index futures contracts.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":68,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/12/5523d96a696568862503b777375e6c65/eb37e1c8caf6bdfc9cc26f120a3a5326/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":34,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/12/5523d96a696568862503b777375e6c65/eb37e1c8caf6bdfc9cc26f120a3a5326/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":9},{"columns":[{"text":"**h.** Since the company is based in the United States, they are exposed to the risk of the Swiss franc appreciating in value. In order to offset possible losses due to the appreciation of value of Swiss francs, the company needs to buy futures contracts of Swiss francs. ","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":143,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/12/5523d96a696568862503b777375e6c65/bc28f3f0f2fe75ca12b4d1609ecf4e70/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":72,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/12/5523d96a696568862503b777375e6c65/bc28f3f0f2fe75ca12b4d1609ecf4e70/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":10},{"columns":[{"text":"**i.**  Since the company is based outside the United States, they are exposed to the risk of the euro depreciating in value. In order to offset possible losses due to the depreciation of value of euros, the company needs to sell futures contracts of euros. ","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":138,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/12/5523d96a696568862503b777375e6c65/717e1466b9fb416e67879349e9afaf24/lateximg_large.png","width":996},"regular":{"height":70,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/12/5523d96a696568862503b777375e6c65/717e1466b9fb416e67879349e9afaf24/lateximg.png","width":499}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":11}],"rating":0,"solutionUuid":"dea1dc06-5272-48d8-a015-8c0abadaa248","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":11}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBeIndexableForSeo":true,"modified":1665448474394,"active":true,"publisher":"McGraw-Hill Education","mainTextbookIsbn":null,"subjects":{"level1":["Social Scienc